    "Scenes, correspondingly, refer to coherent segments of a video that depict a specific event or sequence of actions happening in a continuous time frame, often within a particular setting.",
    "Since ADs are typically inserted during silent moments between dialogues to avoid interference with the ongoing narration-a task that is relatively straightforward-this survey does not delve deeply into techniques for identifying specific video frames for AD insertion.",
    "Instead, we focus on reviewing VFE and DCG methodologies to improve AD generation quality, particularly with the integration of LLMs/VLMs.",
    "Next, in Section 2.1 and 2.2, we provide a summary of the relevant VFE and DCG methodologies that can be applied to AD generation.",
    "We list relevant studies in Table 1."
